==English==

===Etymology===
1800's usage, probably from the imagery that eggshells are easily broken when less cared.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|walks on eggshells|walking on eggshells|walked on eggshells}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To be overly [[careful]] in dealing with a person or situation because they get [[angry]] or [[offended]] very easily; to try very hard not to [[upset]] someone or something.
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To be careful and [[sensitive]], in handling very sensitive matters.

